  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A ***refrain*** is a line, phrase, or group of lines repeated at intervals throughout a [poem](../../../terms/poem.md). It is the structural device that gives many fixed forms their identity — the [villanelle](./villanelle.md) is built from two refrains that alternate and converge; the [pantoum](./pantoum.md) recycles every line as a refrain in a subsequent [stanza](./stanza.md).",
